  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Inscription for the Completion and Celebration of the Dharma Lotus Sutra Assembly at Gaekrim Temple in Wonju
  author: Byeon Gyeryiang
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Gaekrim Temple is hallowed ground where imperial footsteps have trod,
    And the Dharma Lotus Sutra—the true word spoken by the Buddha himself.
    Fitting that a sacred place should host a sacred assembly.

    Reflecting upon the grace bestowed by the sovereign,
    I have dwelt within this temple of renown.
    What was decayed, we have renewed;
    What was broken, we have made whole.
    Seek the merit of rejoicing, that all may contribute.

    In half a year's time,
    The halls for Buddha and quarters for monks rose high into heaven.
    Earth spirits and celestial dragons kept watch,
    Their presence flickering even in the sovereign's dreams.
    This is the fruit of karmic bonds,
    The blessing that descended from the throne.

    Now we celebrate this consecration,
    Unrolling the transcendent dharma gathering.
    One stick of incense rises,
    Filling the ten directions with fragrance.
    The three gates of meditation shine forth,
    Revealing the sinews binding all dharmas.

    Response follows as shadow follows form—
    No river of sand could measure such merit.

    With utmost reverence, I offer these wishes:
    May the sovereign receive endless blessings,
    Rising eternally as sun and moon.
    Through ten thousand years,
    May you endure as heaven and earth.

    May the queen flourish in good fortune,
    May the heir prince enjoy perpetual health and happiness.
    May the six atmospheric forces harmonize,
    That wind and rain arrive in their seasons.
    May the five weapons of war be sheathed,
    That court and realm alike know peace.
  footnotes:
    - The 'three gates of meditation' (三觀) refers to the Tendai Buddhist concept of observing emptiness, temporality, and the middle way simultaneously.
    - The reference to 'ten directions' (十方) encompasses all realms of existence in Buddhist cosmology.
    - '''Merit of rejoicing'' (隨喜) is a Buddhist practice of generating positive karma by celebrating others'' virtuous deeds.'
